Inland Empire: The Headless FALN Rider -- he could appear at any minute!
You: "I'm just going to wait a few more minutes, just in case."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's go. It's very late -- we should be resting already. Tomorrow will be another tough day."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, it would have been *very* cool." The lieutenant nods. "Now let's get some rest."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good. It's already late, we need to get some rest. Tomorrow will be another tough day."
You: "No, we're just passing through."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good. It's late, we should get some rest."
Inland Empire: Your ears hum from the silence inside your mind...
You: There's nothing here -- You lied to me!
Inland Empire: Yes, stay! What's a few more minutes going to hurt?
Inland Empire: Don't listen to the lieutenant! He doesn't know *anything*.
You: "Absolutely not. That's not why we're here. Why would you even think that?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "No one's actually *seen* the Headless FALN Rider because he doesn't exist. He's an urban legend. A *legend*, meaning a story that's not real."
You: "You're right, what was I thinking? Let's go." [Leave.]
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant has his arms crossed, fingers tapping against his bicep. "There, we waited. Nothing happened. Happy now?"
You: "We'll just wait and see."
Kim Kitsuragi: "...a foolish hope. But it's okay. I get it. It would have been *cool*." The lieutenant nods. "Now let's get some rest."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We've been running around together doing *odd things* for days. I've seen how your mind operates... this is just the sort of thing it would latch on to."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant nods.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I know myths and legends are enticing, but in the end they're just stories for children... to teach them lessons, or to frighten them." He gestures toward the waves.
You: "Okay, you got me. I had a hope..."
You: "Yeah, you're right. Would've been cool, though, don't you think?"
You: "How would you know?"
You: "This has made me unspeakably unhappy."
Kim Kitsuragi: "There's nothing to wait for. We should get some rest, it's been a long day."
You: "You were right, Kim. What was I thinking? Let's go." [Leave.]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Please tell me we're not here to look for a headless man in a tracksuit riding a horse... because there's no such thing."
You: "I admit... it is a thing I would *usually* do. But not this time."
